The paper deals with the problem of fair and efficient allocation of goods, which is a central topic in game theory (cs.GT) and economics (cs.EC). The use of budgets and prices to allocate goods suggests a connection to mechanism design (cs.DS) and artificial intelligence (cs.AI). The paper also presents mathematical results on the existence of equilibria, which suggests a connection to optimization and mathematical programming (cs.LG).
